are, 1st Viscount Blakenham|<small>The Right Honourable</small><br>'''John Hare'''<br><small>OBE</small>]]<br><small>MP for [[Sudbury and Woodbridge (UK Parliament constituency)|Sudbury and Woodbridge]]<br>(1911\u20131982)</small>\n| <small>6 January</small><br>1958\n| <small>27 July</small><br>1960\n| {{Party shading/Conservative (UK)}} | [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]]\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-john-hare/ |title=Mr John Hare |website=Hansard 1803\u20132005 |publisher=UK Parliament |accessdate=26 November 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=2 style=\"background-color: {{Conservative Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |\n| rowspan=2 | [[File:No image.svg|75px]]\n| rowspan=2 | [[Christopher Soames|<small>The Right Honourable</small><br>'''Christopher Soames'''<br><small>CBE</small>]]<br><small>MP for [[Bedford (UK Parliament constituency)|Bedford]]<br>(1920\u20131987)</small>\n| rowspan=2 | <small>27 July</small><br>1960\n| rowspan=2 | <small>16 October</small><br>1964\n| rowspan=2 {{Party shading/Conservative (UK)}} | [[Conservative Party (UK)|Conservative]]\n| rowspan=2 | <ref>{{cite web|url=http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-christopher-soames/ |title=Mr Christopher Soames |website=Hansard 1803\u20132005 |publisher=UK Parliament |accessdate=26 November 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| {{Party shading/Conservative (UK)}} | [[Conservative government, 1957\u20131964|Douglas-Home]]\n|-\n| style=\"background-color: {{Labour Party (UK)/meta/color}}\" |\n| [[File:No image.svg|75px]]\n| [[Fred Peart, Baron Peart|<small>The Right Honourable</small><br>'''Fred Peart''']]<br><small>MP for [[Workington (UK Parliament constituency)|Workington]]<br>(1914\u20131988)</small>\n| <small>16 October</small><br>1964\n| <small>6 April</small><br>1968\n| {{Party shading/Labour}} | [[Labour Party (UK)|Labour]]\n| rowspan=2 {{Party shading/Labour}} |[[Labour government, 1964\u20131970|Wilson<br><small>(I & II)</small>]]\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://hansard.