us=dead }}</ref>\n\nFor sponsorship reasons, the league was known as the Sydenhams Wessex League.<ref name=\"FCHD\">{{cite web|url=http://www.fchd.info/lghist/wessex2010.htm |title=2009\u201310 Wessex League |accessdate=20 February 2014 |publisher=FCHD}}</ref>\n\n==League tables==\n===Premier Division===\nThe Premier Division consisted of 22 clubs, the same as the previous season, after [[Sholing F.C.|VT]] were promoted to the [[Southern Football League|Southern League]], and [[Folland Sports F.C.|Hamble A.S.S.C.]] and [[Horndean F.C.|Horndean]] were relegated to Division One. Three new clubs joined:<ref name=\"FCHD\" />\n*[[Blackfield & Langley F.C.|Blackfield & Langley]], runners-up in Division One.\n*[[Totton & Eling F.C.|Totton & Eling]], champions of Division One.\n*[[Winchester City F.C.|Winchester City]], relegated from the Southern League.\n\n{{fb cl header|sort=y}}\n|-\n|1||align=left|[[Poole Town F.C.|Poole Town]] '''(C)'''||42||35||4||3||128||40||+88||109\n|- bgcolor=ccffcc\n|2||align=left|[[Wimborne Town F.C.|Wimborne Town]] '''(P)'''||42||29||4||9||113||43||+70||91||align=left|Joined the [[Southern Football League|Southern League]]\n|-\n|3||align=left|[[Bemerton Heath Harlequins F.C.|Bemerton Heath Harlequins]]||42||28||7||7||84||48||+36||91\n|-\n|4||align=left|[[Bournemouth F.C.|Bournemouth]]||42||27||7||8||87||49||+38||88\n|-\n|5||align=left|[[Christchurch F.C.|Christchurch]]||42||22||12||8||91||66||+25||78\n|-\n|6||align=left|[[Fareham Town F.C.|Fareham Town]]||42||23||7||12||72||53||+19||76\n|-\n|7||align=left|[[Totton & Eling F.C.|Totton & Eling]]||42||22||8||12||69||52||+17||74\n|-\n|8||align=left|[[Blackfield & Langley F.C.|Blackfield & Langley]]||42||20||6||16||74||68||+6||66\n|-\n|9||align=left|[[Newport (IOW) F.C.|Newport (IOW)]]||42||15||14||13||61||55||+6||59\n|-\n|10||align=left|[[Romsey Town F.C.|Romsey Town]]||42||15||13||14||64||57||+7||58\n|-\n|11||align=left|[[Winchester City F.C.|Winchester City]]||42||13||18||11||66||59||+7||57\n|-\n