(WHO) on 11 March 2020.<ref name=\"WHOpandemic2\">{{cite web |url=https://www.who.int/dg/speeches/detail/who-director-general-s-opening-remarks-at-the-media-briefing-on-covid-19---11-march-2020 |title=WHO Director-General's opening remarks at the media briefing on COVID-19 \u2013 11 March 2020 |date=11 March 2020 |publisher=[[World Health Organization]]|access-date=11 March 2020}}</ref> As of 4 April, more than 1,100,000 cases of COVID-19 have been reported in over 220<!--USE BROAD FIGURES, ROUNDED DOWN TO NEAREST 10--> [[List of countries of the world|countries]] and [[Disputed states|territories]], resulting in more than 83,000 deaths <!--ROUNDED DOWN TO NEAREST MULTIPLE OF 1000--> and 308,000 recoveries.<ref name=\"JHU CSSE\" /><ref name=\"WOM\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/|title=Coronavirus Update (Live): 284,712 Cases and 11,842 Deaths from COVID-19 Virus Outbreak - Worldometer|website=www.worldometers.info}}</ref>\n\n==Comparing the SARS outbreaks==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+Compared Spread of SARS outbreaks (as of 9 April 2020 for SARS-CoV-2)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://bnonews.com/index.php/2020/02/the-latest-coronavirus-cases/|title=Tracking coronavirus: Map, data and timeline|last=News|first=B. N. O.|date=18 February 2020|website=BNO News|access-date=4 March 2020}}</ref>\n!Name\n!Countries \n!Confirmed \n!Deaths\n|-\n|[[2002\u20132004 SARS outbreak]]\n|29 \n|8,000+\n|774\n<br />\n|-\n|[[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n|220+ (includes unrecognized or partially recognized territories) \n|2,000,000+\n|101,579+\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic]]\n* [[SARS outbreak]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{portal bar|Medicine|Viruses|Coronavirus disease 2019|Pandemic}}\n\n[[Category:COVID-19]]\n[[Category:Severe acute respiratory syndrome]]\n[[Category:21st-century epidemics]]\n[[Category:Infectious disease-related lists|SARS]]\n", "name_user": "181.174.67.177", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "",